low."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/181/s3523/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–181, § 3523(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", incorporated the substance of the amendment by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/163/s3502/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–163, § 3502(b)","children":[],"tail":", by amending heading and text of subsec. (f) generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The Secretary may pay to a State maritime academy the costs of fuel used by a vessel provided under this section while used for training.” See 2006 Amendment note below and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/304/s18/a"},"text":"section 18(a) of Pub. L. 109–304","children":[],"tail":", set out as a Legislative Purpose and Construction note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t46/s101"},"text":"section 101 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/163/s3502/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–163, § 3502(b)","children":[],"tail":", which directed the amendment of section 1295c(c)(2) of the former Appendix to this title from which subsec. (f) of this section was derived, was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/181/s3523/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–181, § 3523(b)","children":[],"tail":". See 2008 Amendment note for subsec. (f) and Historical and Revision notes above."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
